name: Verify success/warning message box when adding new/duplicate skills from profile dropdown

testSteps.description: 1: Verify success/warning message box when adding new/duplicate skills from profile dropdown ({Technology name=Windows Clustering, Message box text=Success, Skill name=Windows Clustering, status=new, expected condition=can be})

children.description: Given User has login to myMIS beta
Then Open profile menu list from top right on navbar
Then Select "Skills" from dropdown menu list
And Verify "Add skills window" is visible on the current screen
Then Select "Windows Clustering" from technology dropdown on add skills window
Then Select "Beginner" from "Proficiency" dropdown on add skills window
Then Select "Primary" from "Skill type" dropdown on add skills window
And Enter "6" in "Experience" text field
And Click on "Save button"
Then Verify "Success" message appear in screen
And Verify "Windows Clustering" Skill  is "new" and "can be" added in my skills card
